Package: DRIVE
Type: Package
Title: Doubly Robust Instrumental Variable Estimation for Survival Data with Treatment Switching
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Yangli",
           family = "Liu",
           email = "youngoyangliu@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Simulation and estimation tools for additive-hazards survival models
    with treatment switching. Provides naive comparators (intention-to-treat,
    censoring/removal at switch, and a time-varying treatment model) alongside
    doubly robust instrumental-variable estimators, including a cross-fitted
    variant that accepts user-supplied machine-learning nuisance estimators.
    The estimating equations are solved in C++ via Rcpp/RcppArmadillo.
